  <h1>Piggy Build Mode</h1>
  <p>Create your own Piggy maps with logic, triggers, and custom dialogue using Build Mode!</p>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>ðŸ§° Basic Tools</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Build Mode:</strong> Place blocks, decorations, items, and NPCs.</li>
      <li><strong>Event Mode:</strong> Connect triggers and logic gates to create interactions.</li>
      <li><strong>Save/Load:</strong> Store your maps in slots and reload them anytime.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>ðŸ§  Logic Blocks & Triggers</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Touch Trigger</td><td>Activates when a player touches the block.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Button Trigger</td><td>Activates when a player presses a button.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>If Gate</td><td>Passes signal only if a condition is met.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>AND Gate</td><td>Requires all connected signals to be active.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>OR Gate</td><td>Activates if at least one signal is active.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>NOT Gate</td><td>Inverts the signal: activates when input is off.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Dialogue Block</td><td>Displays text to the player with optional commands.</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>ðŸ’¬ Dialogue Commands</h2>
    <p>Use these commands inside a <code>Dialogue Block</code> to enhance storytelling:</p>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Command</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
      <tr><td><code>!fade</code></td><td>Fades the dialogue text in or out.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>!shake</code></td><td>Shakes the dialogue box for dramatic effect.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>!color red</code></td><td>Changes text color (supports red, blue, green, etc.).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>!wait 2</code></td><td>Waits 2 seconds before showing the next line.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>!clear</code></td><td>Clears previous dialogue instantly.</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>Example:</p>
    <code>!fade<br>Intruder detected...<br>!wait 2<br>Prepare for lockdown.</code>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>ðŸ“š Examples</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Two-button door:</strong> Connect two <code>Button Triggers</code> to an <code>AND Gate</code> and then to a door.</li>
      <li><strong>Trap zone:</strong> Use a <code>Touch Trigger</code> connected to a damage block.</li>
      <li><strong>Story intro:</strong> Use a <code>Dialogue Block</code> with <code>!fade</code> and <code>!wait</code> commands.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

